{{Use Australian English|date=June 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}} {{Infobox legislation | short_title=Euthanasia Laws Act 1997 (Cth) | legislature=[[Parliament of Australia]] | image=Coat of Arms of Australia.svg | long_title=An Act concerning euthanasia | introduced_by=[[Kevin Andrews (politician)|Kevin Andrews]] | datepassed=24 March 1997 | royal_assent=27 March 1997 | date_commenced=27 March 1997 | amendments=''(none)'' | related=[[Rights of the Terminally Ill Act 1995]] (NT) | status=Current }} The '''''Euthanasia Laws Act 1997''''' (Cth) is an Act of the [[Parliament of Australia]] to amend the ''[[Northern Territory (Self-Government) Act 1978]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Northern Territory (Self-Government) Act 1978|url=http://www.austlii.edu.au/au/legis/cth/consol_act/nta1978425/}}</ref> the [[Australian Capital Territory (Self-Government) Act 1988|''Australian Capital Territory (Self-Government) Act 1988'' (Cth)]] and the [[Norfolk Island Act 1979|''Norfolk Island Act 1979'' (Cth)]] to remove the power of the Parliament of each of those territories to legalise [[euthanasia]]. The law was enacted in response to the enactment by the [[Northern Territory Parliament]] of the [[Rights of the Terminally Ill Act 1995]] (NT) which had legalised euthanasia in the Territory.
The ''Euthanasia Laws Bill 1996'' was introduced in the Australian Parliament by [[Liberal Party of Australia|Liberal Party]] backbencher [[Kevin Andrews (politician)|Kevin Andrews]] as a [[private member's bill]].
